Description: CVE-2026-44631 - ap_regname: restrict to reasonable captures
 Heap buffer underwrite in ap_regname(): a signed char was used to index
 the PCRE capture-name table, so capture-group indices >= 128 wrapped
 negative and caused a heap underwrite. The fix adds bounds checking
 in ap_regname() and propagates its return value at the four call sites.
 .
 CVSS 9.8 (CRITICAL) - CWE-124 Buffer Underwrite.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/httpd/commit/7d9f3cfb10b0fe70df7358d26d7b1f374ea1a0cb
Bug: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-44631
Author: Eric Covener <covener@apache.org>
