Description: CVE-2026-42535 - mod_dav_fs: deny access to DAV state directory
 Apache HTTP Server mod_dav_fs path-handling flaw: dav_fs_get_resource() did
 not refuse access to or within the .DAV state directory (DAV_FS_STATE_DIR).
 An authenticated WebDAV content author could manipulate the state directory
 used by mod_dav_fs to track lock/property metadata, leading to integrity
 and availability impact on resources served via WebDAV.
 .
 This patch refuses access when the leaf or parent path component matches
 DAV_FS_STATE_DIR.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/apache/httpd/commit/56bfb128432a38e2e6bc5448122914bb271b1252
Author: Eric Covener <covener@apache.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-19
